INSERT INTO `wp_eqv5w1_comments` VALUES(123, 425, 'andy loves Jehovah, do you?', 'panlovestink@hotmail.com', 'http://', '69.92.242.42', '2008-02-01 06:07:59', '2008-02-01 06:07:59', 'Lauren, WHAT WAS THAT SONG!? i heard a lot of "nigga" in it.. and a few gd''s :x haha crazy.\n\ngreat video. i love how our stomachs are the stillframe when it''s not playing, lol.\n\nalso, excellent truths, but i disagree with the one about "living in the moment". (just about) every moment is good indeed but i''ve never found it necessary to seriously live in the moment all the time. i think the future needs to be focused on a little bit more than that, at least in a "realistically aware" manner, as opposed to worry and anxiety. some moments are definitely worth dwelling in completely, especially if you are frazzled and stressed about something to come, but (for me) it''s not bad to think about the past now and then or about the future, even for prolonged periods, as long as it''s not a constant or consuming occurrence. example, if i''m flying somewhere and am on a 2 hour layover, by an hour and a half i''m not going to be too excited about living in the moment i''m in. i''m definately going to be focused on getting on the plane and whatever''s going on when i get off the plane, until i get on the plane. and i don''t think that''s a wrong way to dwell my thoughts in a moment like that.\n\nthough once on the plane, i''m definately going to be living in the present, enjoying the beauty of the sky and earth until i land. :)\n\ni agree completely with the rest of them, though :) especially the ones about trust and love. yip.', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 0);
