INSERT INTO `wp_eqv5w1_options` VALUES(349, 0, '_transient_rss_c1f9d0f400ea517c489d96d6a1de1668', 'O:9:"MagpieRSS":17:{s:6:"parser";i:0;s:12:"current_item";a:0:{}s:5:"items";a:3:{i:0;a:13:{s:5:"title";s:32:"Forums are sometimes horribleâ€¦";s:4:"link";s:60:"http://alexrabe.de/2009/12/13/forums-are-sometimes-horrible/";s:8:"comments";s:69:"http://alexrabe.de/2009/12/13/forums-are-sometimes-horrible/#comments";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Sun, 13 Dec 2009 13:29:11 +0000";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:9:"alex.rabe";}s:8:"category";s:28:"AllerleiforumsiPhonevodafone";s:4:"guid";s:25:"http://alexrabe.de/?p=539";s:11:"description";s:385:"A wek ago I&#8217;ve exchanged my HTC Magic &#8220;Android&#8221; phone with the iPhone 3GS. My company would normally provide me a Blackberry, but hey I need a Smart-Internet-laptop-in-your-pocket-and-and-not-just-a-email-client-phone ! So I decided to buy me a (SIM unlocked, legal) iPhone. It was easy to setup with my provider (Vodafone Germany), they provide a good document [...]";s:7:"content";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";s:1745:"<p>A wek ago I&#8217;ve exchanged my HTC Magic &#8220;Android&#8221; phone with the iPhone 3GS. My company would normally provide me a Blackberry, but hey I need a Smart-Internet-laptop-in-your-pocket-and-and-not-just-a-email-client-phone ! So I decided to buy me a (SIM unlocked, legal) iPhone. It was easy to setup with my provider (Vodafone Germany), they provide a good <a href="http://www.vodafone.de/infofaxe/126.pdf">document</a> how to setup my iPhone and all works fine (MMS, Internet, Mailbox , Visual Voicemail is Â not available) but there is one nasty little problem :</p>\n<p>Every time I call or get a call a little popup &#8220;Call forwarding active&#8221; show up&#8230;Really annoying !!!</p>\n<p>Now, I start google a bit around and get real frustrated. There are hundreds of &#8220;fixes&#8221; and &#8220;solutions&#8221; available in some German forums, no one describe the real problem. The most fixes will are only useful for jailbroken iPhone&#8217;sÂ (-&gt; ForwardMSGfix) and a couple of ideas are <a href="http://www.apfeltalk.de/forum/gel-st-vf-t277212.html">really stupid</a>. No one describe why this problem happened and after one hour I found some notes about the &#8220;ShowCallForwarding&#8221; flag in the carrier profile.</p>\n<p>With this information I final found a <a href="http://www.iphone-notes.de/2009/03/22/iphone-os-30-mms-tethering-fur-deutsche-provider/">solution</a> for my iPhone without Jailbreak fixes. I really love the Internet and all it&#8217;s output, but forums are sometimes give you a wrong direction. Some people wrote silly things and it takes hours to get to the root of your problems&#8230;</p>\n<img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/alexrabe/~4/Wk-HQAniXho" height="1" width="1"/>";}s:3:"wfw";a:1:{s:10:"commentrss";s:65:"http://alexrabe.de/2009/12/13/forums-are-sometimes-horrible/feed/";}s:5:"slash";a:1:{s:8:"comments";s:1:"0";}s:7:"summary";s:385:"A wek ago I&#8217;ve exchanged my HTC Magic &#8220;Android&#8221; phone with the iPhone 3GS. My company would normally provide me a Blackberry, but hey I need a Smart-Internet-laptop-in-your-pocket-and-and-not-just-a-email-client-phone ! So I decided to buy me a (SIM unlocked, legal) iPhone. It was easy to setup with my provider (Vodafone Germany), they provide a good document [...]";s:12:"atom_content";s:1745:"<p>A wek ago I&#8217;ve exchanged my HTC Magic &#8220;Android&#8221; phone with the iPhone 3GS. My company would normally provide me a Blackberry, but hey I need a Smart-Internet-laptop-in-your-pocket-and-and-not-just-a-email-client-phone ! So I decided to buy me a (SIM unlocked, legal) iPhone. It was easy to setup with my provider (Vodafone Germany), they provide a good <a href="http://www.vodafone.de/infofaxe/126.pdf">document</a> how to setup my iPhone and all works fine (MMS, Internet, Mailbox , Visual Voicemail is Â not available) but there is one nasty little problem :</p>\n<p>Every time I call or get a call a little popup &#8220;Call forwarding active&#8221; show up&#8230;Really annoying !!!</p>\n<p>Now, I start google a bit around and get real frustrated. There are hundreds of &#8220;fixes&#8221; and &#8220;solutions&#8221; available in some German forums, no one describe the real problem. The most fixes will are only useful for jailbroken iPhone&#8217;sÂ (-&gt; ForwardMSGfix) and a couple of ideas are <a href="http://www.apfeltalk.de/forum/gel-st-vf-t277212.html">really stupid</a>. No one describe why this problem happened and after one hour I found some notes about the &#8220;ShowCallForwarding&#8221; flag in the carrier profile.</p>\n<p>With this information I final found a <a href="http://www.iphone-notes.de/2009/03/22/iphone-os-30-mms-tethering-fur-deutsche-provider/">solution</a> for my iPhone without Jailbreak fixes. I really love the Internet and all it&#8217;s output, but forums are sometimes give you a wrong direction. Some people wrote silly things and it takes hours to get to the root of your problems&#8230;</p>\n<img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/alexrabe/~4/Wk-HQAniXho" height="1" width="1"/>";}i:1;a:13:{s:5:"title";s:20:"No more direct calls";s:4:"link";s:51:"http://alexrabe.de/2009/11/16/no-more-direct-calls/";s:8:"comments";s:60:"http://alexrabe.de/2009/11/16/no-more-direct-calls/#comments";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Mon, 16 Nov 2009 12:17:01 +0000";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:9:"alex.rabe";}s:8:"category";s:30:"NextGEN GalleryNextGEN-Gallery";s:4:"guid";s:25:"http://alexrabe.de/?p=530";s:11:"description";s:303:"In the last weeks I follow a discussion at wp-hackers and trac ticket #11509. Currently I used a couple of direct calls to my plugin , due to the fact that I need to output some AJAX request or a XML content. Joseph Scott says in the trac ticket :\nThe wp-config.php, wp-load.php, etc. files should [...]";s:7:"content";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";s:1140:"<p>In the last weeks I follow a discussion at wp-hackers and trac ticket <a href="http://core.trac.wordpress.org/ticket/11059">#11509</a>. Currently I used a couple of direct calls to my plugin , due to the fact that I need to output some AJAX request or a XML content. Joseph Scott says in the trac ticket :</p>\n<blockquote><p>The wp-config.php, wp-load.php, etc. files should never be directly included by a theme or plugin.</p></blockquote>\n<p>I start thinking what could be the solution for my problems and in the same second I&#8217;ve spined my ideas he linked to an article from <a href="http://willnorris.com/2009/06/wordpress-plugin-pet-peeve-2-direct-calls-to-plugin-files">Will Norris</a>. I never ever get the same idea since I wrote my first plugin, it&#8217;s really simple to realize and a more robust solution. Very stupid that I missed that before&#8230;</p>\n<p>I willÂ start to remove direct calls to my plugins with the next Version 1.4.2. There are more more work on it, so it&#8217;s a first test for the slideshow XML output.</p>\n<img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/alexrabe/~4/TZi56MlumTw" height="1" width="1"/>";}s:3:"wfw";a:1:{s:10:"commentrss";s:56:"http://alexrabe.de/2009/11/16/no-more-direct-calls/feed/";}s:5:"slash";a:1:{s:8:"comments";s:1:"3";}s:7:"summary";s:303:"In the last weeks I follow a discussion at wp-hackers and trac ticket #11509. Currently I used a couple of direct calls to my plugin , due to the fact that I need to output some AJAX request or a XML content. Joseph Scott says in the trac ticket :\nThe wp-config.php, wp-load.php, etc. files should [...]";s:12:"atom_content";s:1140:"<p>In the last weeks I follow a discussion at wp-hackers and trac ticket <a href="http://core.trac.wordpress.org/ticket/11059">#11509</a>. Currently I used a couple of direct calls to my plugin , due to the fact that I need to output some AJAX request or a XML content. Joseph Scott says in the trac ticket :</p>\n<blockquote><p>The wp-config.php, wp-load.php, etc. files should never be directly included by a theme or plugin.</p></blockquote>\n<p>I start thinking what could be the solution for my problems and in the same second I&#8217;ve spined my ideas he linked to an article from <a href="http://willnorris.com/2009/06/wordpress-plugin-pet-peeve-2-direct-calls-to-plugin-files">Will Norris</a>. I never ever get the same idea since I wrote my first plugin, it&#8217;s really simple to realize and a more robust solution. Very stupid that I missed that before&#8230;</p>\n<p>I willÂ start to remove direct calls to my plugins with the next Version 1.4.2. There are more more work on it, so it&#8217;s a first test for the slideshow XML output.</p>\n<img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/alexrabe/~4/TZi56MlumTw" height="1" width="1"/>";}i:2;a:13:{s:5:"title";s:13:"Revision 6892";s:4:"link";s:44:"http://alexrabe.de/2009/11/14/revision-6892/";s:8:"comments";s:53:"http://alexrabe.de/2009/11/14/revision-6892/#comments";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Sat, 14 Nov 2009 12:50:53 +0000";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:9:"alex.rabe";}s:8:"category";s:6:"Common";s:4:"guid";s:25:"http://alexrabe.de/?p=402";s:11:"description";s:80:"\nToday, three years ago created Matt my first plugin account (wp-table)&#8230;.\n";s:7:"content";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";s:476:"<p><a rel="attachment wp-att-403" href="http://alexrabe.de/2009/11/14/revision-6892/subversion/"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-403" title="subversion" src="http://alexrabe.de/wp-content/uploads/subversion.png" alt="subversion" width="466" height="138" /></a></p>\n<p>Today, three years ago created <a href="http://ma.tt/">Matt</a> my first plugin account (wp-table)&#8230;.</p>\n<img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/alexrabe/~4/4t9kN7HfGR0" height="1" width="1"/>";}s:3:"wfw";a:1:{s:10:"commentrss";s:49:"http://alexrabe.de/2009/11/14/revision-6892/feed/";}s:5:"slash";a:1:{s:8:"comments";s:1:"0";}s:7:"summary";s:80:"\nToday, three years ago created Matt my first plugin account (wp-table)&#8230;.\n";s:12:"atom_content";s:476:"<p><a rel="attachment wp-att-403" href="http://al