INSERT INTO `wp_eqv5w1_posts` VALUES(536, 2, '2008-04-03 04:22:00', '2008-04-03 04:22:00', 'I can''t believe how blessed I am right now to have such incredible people in my house. I''ve been struggling for a little while wondering where "home" is and I think this time, I''ve really solved it. As much as we say home is where the heart is, it''s really true. And my heart is not in a place - it''s with the people that I love. Home is where the people I love are. If I truly know who I deeply love, that''s where I want to be and where home is. So regardless if I''m on the road, I can have a little bit of home wherever I''m at.\n\nIt was hard at times in the past months traveling alone more often than not... and not having familiar faces. Not that I don''t <em>love</em> meeting new people - I do - I just didn''t have enough "home" in my life on a consistent basis. It made my heart ache and messed with me a bit.\n\nI even wrote recently about all of this, and now, after experiencing a pretty intense period of time continually ''going it alone'' - I''m more thankful than ever for the people that are here with me.\n\n<a href="http://myspace.com/danieldixon">Daniel</a> (who I naturally call, Dan) moved here only two days ago from Louisville, KY. <a href="http://jessicagrady.wordpress.com">Jess</a>, Brittany and I were in Nashville from Wed til Sunday and helped him move here on Monday. The last two days of the trip were quite exhausting... but worth it. He now resides in my basement... yes, my basement. He''s here for an estimated 2 months.\n\n<a href="http://myspace.com/andrewstonestreet">Â Andrew </a>and Dan are working on the new business (Green Light District) unfolding at a steady, rapid pace. I''m getting to know and love beautiful <a href="http://jessicagrady.wordpress.com">Jessica Grady</a> who has graciously assisted me on recent photo shoots in Nashville and one to come this weekend in Raleigh/Wilmington, NC. Her heart is HUGE and SO FULL. I can''t wait to see what''s coming for her... it''s going to be nothing short of amazing.\n\nI''ve got A LOT of goals for this year - a lot of vision - and a lot of it has already come to pass. I can''t believe it. Right now, I''ll admit, things are pretty crazy... making it financially, helping out the family any way I can, trying to be there for ones I love, work just enough and not too much (balance is key), have my time of solitude every week where I re-think everything (so I never get stuck in one thing - one way of thinking or doing things - there''s always something better, something to learn; growing) and soak it all in (which, by the way, I have been doing! and it''s been awesome), booking shoots at home and away, dabbling in new forms of photography and art (painting, mixed media, writing on piano more), and realizing (again/more so), that I have sooo many art forms that I''m passionate about that I don''t want to fade (ie: dance/choreography, writing)... trying to figure out how to incorporate those...Â  and BIG art projects that are<em> right </em>under my skin about to burst. I may take off the summer months and hide away from the lime light in a way. We''ll see.\n\nThere are so many obstacles in front of me right now that very well look like they could hold me back from what I need to do - a lot of it being finances. New photo gear is not a small thing. We''re talking at least $8,000 if not more just to start out - and I know it''s the direction I need to head in.\n\n<em>Eh</em>. <strong>Stop.</strong> How did I start rambling about all of this? : )\n\nOkay, so when I started this post.. I had one thing in mind. God has been speaking so clearly to my heart over the past week about one thing. I don''t even know how to describe it. All I know, is that regardless of ALLL this going on in my head/heart, I''ve got this peace. A "big change" is coming in the next month,<em> I feel it. </em>I''ve had it confirmed time and time again.\n\nIt all started this past Sunday when someone told me straight up, "Lauren - you''re in strength training... You''ve got a lot on you, and it looks like it could destroy you, but it''s about to fall off - and when you really head up the mountain ahead of you, it''ll be with ease."\n\nI know exactly what strength training feels like. I used to be a hardcore swim team member back in the day - we''d prepare for our biggest meets by wearing tennis shoes, big t-shirts and old jeans in 2-hr practices weeks before the meet.... and a few days before, we''d shed it all at practice.... including valuable seconds.\n\nTime and time again, this was confirmed (strength training, the ''big change'') to me in, sometimes, the funniest ways... We were all driving to Louisville on Sunday, hoping to make it to church on time (since we''d all hadn''t been to church in awhile; and wanted to be at <a href="http://www.sojournchurch.com/">Sojourn</a>). We left from Nashville in plenty of time to make it. But, amazingly, we got stuck in the most crazy traffic ever...<strong> 9 miles every 45 minutes. No lie.</strong> Apparently, we didn''t make it to church.\n\nAfter 2-ish hours of this car to car traffic continued, I was starting to go crazy. Jess was perfectly fine - she''s an LA-native. This was cake. I was not used to this as much. We had a dance party in the car, and with other cars in other lanes (video to be posted later to prove it). Anyway, when we came around the corner and saw the END of the traffic... we were freaking out. It was literally only about a 1/4 a mile of work happening that caused it. <em>Dumb.</em> When we cleared it, I seriously gunned it to over 80... the windows were rolled down, the Bee Gees were blasting, and we were screaming/laughing (haha, I''m laughing just thinking about it!). I can''t fully describe to you that feeling of release - but I felt as though I shed layers of skin. We had church in the car, no doubt. The traffic sucked, but it was so good. I feel like I''m stuck in traffic where I''m at right now in life, and when I finally break through, ohhh what''ll happen ; )\n\nThis post is long. But I haven''t posted anything worth while in awhile. So, yeah.\n\n<strong>Catching you</strong> <strong>up:</strong>\n- I''m in Raleigh/Wilmington, NC this weekend shooting the beautiful, Jodi - upcoming bride!\n-<em>Next week</em>: eddddddit week. Dreading it. Pray for me? ; )\n-Some family, senior and dance shoots next weekend. Yay.\n-April 17-20: Potentially in San Francisco with Dan for <a href="http://myspace.com/thecobaltseason">The Cobalt Season</a> CD release show\n-Shoots the last weekend in April at home\n-May 2-4: Shooting Brentley and Jodi''s Wedding in NC\n\n...I think that''s enough for now : ) I''m booked until mid-June, taking time off and just traveling doing some photo journalism projects for the <a href="http://www.openarmsfoundation.com/">Open Arms Foundation</a> in Medellin, Columbia, South America in July. In August - some major opportunities, looking into them; Sept - South Africa/London; Oct - moving month; and weddings.\n\nShew. I feel like I''ve already lived until Oct. So much to come this year, so much.\n\n<strong>Catch up on my recent work <a href="http://flickr.com/photos/elle_effect">HERE</a>. It''s not all up yet - I''m working on it! </strong>\n\n<strong>Â </strong>\n\nthanks for reading this mumble jumbled mess of thought.\n\nI''m learning to take in <em>every</em> moment, have the past fuel my future, and truly see the familiar again as if it were the first time - because once something is familiar, we often become blind. I never want to be blind. I want a <a href="http://myspace.com/brookewaggoner">fresh pair of eyes</a>.\n\nlove.\n-lauren', 'no pictures, just words. jumbled, needed words.', '', 'private', 'open', 'open', '', 'no-pictures-just-words-jumbled-needed-words', '', '', '2008-04-03 04:22:00', '2008-04-03 04:22:00', '', 0, 'http://laurensusanna.wordpress.com/?p=536', 0, 'post', '', 3);
INSERT INTO `wp_eqv5w1_posts` VALUES(537, 2, '2008-04-04 23:37:25', '2008-04-04 23:37:25', 'The drive here was so refreshing... it felt like such a smooth, short drive - but it took about 6 hours. The scenery took my breath away, and I felt so small, so content within the moment, so overwhelmed all at the same time.\n\nWe''re stopped here in Raleigh where we met Jodi, the wonderful girl I''m taking bridal photos of tomorrow, and we''re heading down to Wilmington tonight ready for an early shoot in the morning. I feel my heart changing a continual pace for the better... I''ve been going to sleep every night this week with the thought, "wow, His grace <em>really</em> is new every morning."\n\nI was not really wanting to hop in the car and drive when I woke up this morning. But once we started out, sat in the silence for awhile (which I''m learning doesn''t always have to be an uncomfortable thing), and had this great time just talking with each other and God back and forth for about an hour... I felt good. Right where I was supposed to be in that moment.\n\n...I''ll have to finish all these thoughts later. We''re leaving her apt for Wilmington. Heading to her Mom''s house for some gooood southern cookin''. <em>Oh, thank you Lord : ) </em>\n\n-lauren', 'sitting here in north carolina...', '', 'private', 'open', 'open', '', 'sitting-here-in-north-carolina', '', '', '2008-04-04 23:37:25', '2008-04-04 23:37:25', '', 0, 'http://laurensusanna.wordpress.com/?p=537', 0, 'post', '', 2);
INSERT INTO `wp_eqv5w1_posts` VALUES(539, 2, '2008-04-06 05:10:00', '2008-04-06 05:10:00', '<img src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2053/2391799248_2a1c396df8.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="332" />\n\nrefreshing yet long day. I''ve driven 13hrs in 2 days.\n\nCharleston to Raleigh, Raleigh to Wilson. Sleep.\nWilson to Wilmington. Wilmington to Raleigh... current location.\n\nSo many adventures today - I''ll debrief more tomorrow. Right now, I neeeed sleeep.\n\n- lauren', 'wilmington, NC', '', 'private', 'open', 'open', '', 'wilmington-nc', '', '', '2008-04-06 05:10:00', '2008-04-06 05:10:00', '', 0, 'http://laurensusanna.wordpress.com/?p=539', 0, 'post', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `wp_eqv5w1_posts` VALUES(540, 2, '2008-04-06 06:05:58', '2008-04-06 06:05:58', 'I''ve noticed there has been a lack of posts... <em>shrugs</em>. I''d rather experience it than post it, I''d rather write it in my tangible journal first, and one of these days - I will pour what I''ve been learning at a rapid and continual pace.\n\njust thought I''d go ahead and add that.\n\nand this:\n\n<img src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2167/2391056383_1242bb7c44.jpg" alt="" />\n\nmaybe in this photo you can see how my heart is good.\n\nor in this:\n\n<img src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2306/2391889338_e83009599a.jpg" alt="" />\n\nha. thanks to my girl, <a href="http://jessicagrady.wordpress.com">jessica</a>.', 'and oh:', '', 'private', 'open', 'open', '', 'and-oh', '', '', '2008-04-06 06:05:58', '2008-04-06 06:05:58', '', 0, 'http://laurensusanna.wordpress.com/?p=540', 0, 'post', '', 3);
INSERT INTO `wp_eqv5w1_posts` VALUES(545, 2, '2008-04-08 21:13:09', '2008-04-08 21:13:09', 'This morning I''m staring at a compost pile nearby after a brisk walk. It seems out of place with it surroundings... I got to thinking about it... and it hit me how it looks and appears to be a bunch of old banana peels, fruit, tomatoes; all things rotting, really; and hw they will melt and mold and rot together in a big, stinky pile of make... <strong>rich soil.</strong> <em>Rich soil?!</em> Yes - rich soil. Nothing poor or lacking about it.\n\nI''m like that compost pile. A lot of things complied - rotting, melting and molding together for my good. And it will, in time, turn into rich soil. Not a thing lacking. But... for the rich soil not to waste, I must then plant good things in it. I''m being prepared and conditioned for something greater than myself and will no longer allow myself to think or be stunted in any way... this process is aching and it is glorious.', 'a little wisdom in the simple', '', 'private', 'open', 'open', '', 'a-little-wisdom-in-the-simple', '', '', '2008-04-08 21:13:09', '2008-04-08 21:13:09', '', 0, 'http://laurensusanna.wordpress.com/?p=545', 0, 'post', '', 1);
INSERT INTO `wp_eqv5w1_posts` VALUES(546, 2, '2008-04-10 06:50:12', '2008-04-10 06:50:12', '<p style="text-align:center;"><img src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3209/2400706067_ee0c134406.jpg" alt="" /></p>\n<p style="text-align:center;">these people have been so good for me/to me:</p>\n<p style="text-align:center;"><img src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3233/2401848107_5eea17f622.jpg" alt="" /></p>\nSO many shoots to finish editing by Saturday. I''ve been working, working, working... trying to enjoy being with the people around me, sort through the things in my heart and create. Once I finish all these past couple weeks shoots, I''ve got a packed next couple weeks here at home (and maybe back in Nashville), then back in beautiful NC for Brentley and Jodi''s wedding. Very excited about it - it was so good to be able to see the locations and scout while I was down there last weekend. I just need a few things before shooting it - 35mm f/1.8 and 2 more memory cards. <em>Doable.</em>\n\nA few photos of past shoots I''ve been working on (more to come):\n\n<img src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2412/2401471248_07acfb600f.jpg" alt="" />\n\n<img src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2137/2401470838_96507740fd.jpg" alt="" />\n\n<a href="http://www.myspace.com/calebmaitland">caleb maitland</a>\n\n<img src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2207/2380958493_f3c11c8432.jpg" alt="" />\n\n<img src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3101/2380958169_afafc41c7b.jpg" alt="" />\n\n<img src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2305/2381791814_7f5b73ee3f.jpg" alt="" />\n\n<img src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3254/2380957511_a3f1e0bbb8.jpg" alt="" />\n\n<a href="http://myspace.com/elizabethstanley">liz stanley</a>\nmakeup, styling, body paint: <a href="http://myspace.com/vote4christin">christin cook</a>\nphotography, styling and post pro: myself\nassistants and visionaries: <a href="http://jessicagrady.wordpress.com">jessica grady</a> and brittany yates\n\nAlso, Tuesday morning was <strong>glorious</strong>. I spent 2-3 hours straight sitting on an old tree root overlooking my small, humble town in silence... writing in my journal, listening, being still... things that need to be practiced on a continual basis. Things I love and value. It was so good for my soul - I actually <em>felt</em> the goodness of God resting on me... how undeserving am I.\n<p style="text-align:center;"><img src="http://i71.photobucket.com/albums/i122/elle_effect_photography/L_1731.jpg" alt="" width="392" height="589" /></p>\n<p style="text-align:center;"><img src="http://i71.photobucket.com/albums/i122/elle_effect_photography/L_1758.jpg" alt="" width="383" height="254" /></p>\n<p style="text-align:center;"><img src="http://i71.photobucket.com/albums/i122/elle_effect_photography/2402678880_44e2ff4cea.jpg" alt="" /></p>\n<p style="text-align:center;">jessica makes me laugh... and peeks well.</p>\n<p style="text-align:center;"><img src="http://i71.photobucket.com/albums/i122/elle_effect_photography/jld_1853.jpg" alt="" width="344" height="518" /></p>\n<p style="text-align:center;">Â </p>\n<p style="text-align:center;">Â </p>', '&gt;&gt;&gt;', '', 'private', 'open', 'open', '', '546', '', '', '2008-04-10 06:50:12', '2008-04-10 06:50:12', '', 0, 'http://laurensusanna.wordpress.com/?p=546', 0, 'post', '', 1);
INSERT INTO `wp_eqv5w1_posts` VALUES(548, 2, '2008-04-12 04:34:39', '2008-04-12 04:34:39', '<img src="http://i71.photobucket.com/albums/i122/elle_effect_photography/LW_1362.jpg" alt="" width="527" height="350" />\n\nen route to NC somewhere in VA. take the scenic routes.\n\nmore photos of our trip <a href="http://www.facebook.com/album.php?aid=2000145&amp;l=7038d&amp;id=1592310016">here.</a>', 'these are good days', '', 'private', 'open', 'open', '', 'these-are-good-days', '', '', '2008-04-12 04:34:39', '2008-04-12 04:34:39', '', 0, 'http://laurensusanna.wordpress.com/?p=548', 0, 'post', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `wp_eqv5w1_posts` VALUES(553, 2, '2008-04-16 23:36:02', '2008-04-16 23:36:02', '''tis the season for senior portraits... Michael started the wonderful madness this week:\n\n<a title="michael by elle_effect, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/elle_effect/2419640904/"><img src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3253/2419640904_09eeae8ace.jpg" alt="michael" width="500" height="332" /></a>\n\n<a title="michael by elle_effect, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/elle_effect/2419640662/"><img src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2011/2419640662_e58e714886.jpg" alt="michael" width="332" height="500" /></a>\n\n<a title="michael by elle_effect, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/elle_effect/2417301977/"></a>\n<a title="michael by elle_effect, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/elle_effect/2417301733/"><img src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3120/2417301733_7da30579cd.jpg" alt="michael" width="332" height="500" /></a>\n\nÂ \n\nand a little vid for fun:\n\n[youtube=http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7sTC-KWZnxc]\n\nJess and Dan leave for San Fransisco early in the morning. They''ll be gone for a week - and they''ll definitely be missed. It''s been an amazing month... full of its share of ups and downs, but it''s definitely made me stronger in ways I never thought possible. You know when you haven''t exercised in... let''s say, months... and then you decide to jump back into a new routine of exercising again - welllll you''ll definitely feel muscles you forgot were there/didn''t know where there ; ) That''s a pretty clear depiction of what''s been happening - and it''s been so good.\n\nI''ve been reading a little bit of ''Thirsty'' - a collection of poetry by Mary Oliver (thanks to Dan), finishing ''What is the What'' by Dave Eggers, and starting a new way of reading the Word every day... I''ve been lacking in the daily-reading dept, and I think I''ve finally changed my pace.\n\nOkay, Target run about the happen... Grocery store run to finish Chicken ''n Biscuits for dinner. And ohhh, it''s been great to cook again. Sunday night, we had a dinner party here at the house - Jess, Dan, Andrew, Britt, Lydia, Bradley, John and myself were here - Dan, Jess, Bradley and I got the good, the ladies (plus the wonderful Bradley) cooked the meal and we partook... ahh, so good! We made a vegetable pasta of sorts - zucchini, yellow squash, onion, red pepper, tomatoes; tossed with angel hair pasta; white wine, olive oil and our choice of spices made the light sauce; asparagus on the side. mm, mm, mmmm. I want it again right now just talking about it!\n\nSigur Ros film happened - <em>ohhhh, Sigur Ros : )</em> Last night, another film - "Into the Wild" - was watched... It kinda messed me up, in a good way. I was definitely glued to the screen.\n\n...and I can''t wait to show you all the bridal shots of Jodi in a few weeks ; )\n-lauren', 'update + senior portraits', '', 'private', 'open', 'open', '', 'update-senior-portraits', '', '', '2008-04-16 23:36:02', '2008-04-16 23:36:02', '', 0, 'http://laurensusanna.wordpress.com/?p=553', 0, 'post', '', 4);
INSERT INTO `wp_eqv5w1_posts` VALUES(554, 2, '2008-04-17 21:11:36', '2008-04-17 21:11:36', 'Sigh, I am tired. I love photography, ohh I really do. I <strong>adore</strong> it. I don''t want it to loose any of its spark. Sometimes, you have to switch up the artistic mediums a bit. Yes, I have been painting some. Yes, I still choreograph. Yes, I play piano every single day when I can, and when I can''t, I crave it. I''m craving for the things that make me alive. As always, I''m reevaluating why I create, what I love and who I strive to be. It''s healthy to be continually humbled in all that you do. I am more than blessed to do what I do - and have come so far even only looking back over this past year.\n\nSometimes, you just need to sit. Silent. Reflect on how far you''ve come and appreciate your work. Once you''re finished and gleamed what you will - you move forward with more ''umph'' and drive - a new kick of alive; something fresh. I''ve wanted to do this recently.. but I''ve been unable to do it to the extent that I would like to. Right now it''s only reflection in bite size pieces - but I need something lengthy pretty soon.\n\nSo, remember to reflect... it''s one of the most important things in creating and being an artist.\n\n[I am writing this, just now getting home 20 minutes ago; 3 hours of sleep last night; woke up at 4AM to take Jess and Dan to the Columbus airport; spent a little time seeing a good friend and headed back home; it''s been quite the long day]\n\n-lauren', 'in need to reflect...', '', 'private', 'open', 'open', '', 'in-need-to-reflect', '', '', '2008-04-17 21:11:36', '2008-04-17 21:11:36', '', 0, 'http://laurensusanna.wordpress.com/?p=554', 0, 'post', '', 2);
INSERT INTO `wp_eqv5w1_posts` VALUES(555, 2, '2008-04-18 19:21:33', '2008-04-18 19:21:33', 'I was able to meet briefly, <a href="http://michaelwintersart.com">Michael WInters</a>, at <a href="http://www.consuminglouisville.com/2007/10/quills-coffee-books.php">Quills</a> in Louisville, KY. I am intirgued by his photography as well as his wife, <a href="http://mickiewintersart.com">Mickie''s</a>.\n\nI''m hoping to purchase someÂ prints from Mickie''s "Bend" series - whichÂ strikes a strong chord with me, since I am a dancer as well a photographer. She captured the movement<em>Â so</em> beautifully.\n\nTo look at the series - simply go to <a href="http://mickiewinterart.com">Mickie''s website</a>, click <strong>archives</strong>, and type in the password box, <strong>BEND</strong>.\n\n-lauren', 'Michael and Mickie Winters', '', 'private', 'open', 'open', '', 'michael-and-mickie-winters', '', '', '2008-04-18 19:21:33', '2008-04-18 19:21:33', '', 0, 'http://laurensusanna.wordpress.com/?p=555', 0, 'post', '', 4);
INSERT INTO `wp_eqv5w1_posts` VALUES(556, 2, '2008-04-23 03:37:26', '2008-04-23 03:37:26', 'What a wonderful girl - she seriously blessed me on Sunday afternoon when we headed out together to do her shoot. She''s so talented, graduating, and her heart is exploding with creativity. I''m sure she didn''t even realize when she encouraged my heart when she quickly stated, "It''s incredible you''re able to be a photographer... the world is your canvas. You can do <em>anything. you. want.</em>"\n\n...and just to warn you, as I have changed, so has my photography and it will be taking a new form in the next few months. I may back off from blogging as much. Solitude calls me again. It''s all brewing and has been for quite sometime.\n\nA little excerpt of the email she sent me after the shoot that made me smile:\n\n"<em>I very much enjoyed my afternoon....and the creepers, and the big guy questioning our motives on the dilapidated house of awesome, and the exploding/mystery marble floating Japanese Jones drinks :)</em>"\n\nYep. We have fun on shoots. ; )\n\nLearning a lot more, trying to apply it - some photos from Sunday:\n\n<a title="rachel by elle_effect, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/elle_effect/2434998061/"><img src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2132/2434998061_df033ba6f0.jpg" alt="rachel" width="500" height="476" /></a>\n\n<a title="rachel by elle_effect, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/elle_effect/2434997911/"><img src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3025/2434997911_382c6da98e.jpg" alt="rachel" width="500" height="332" /></a>\n\n<a title="rachel by elle_effect, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/elle_effect/2435814848/"><img src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2019/2435814848_db7a098580.jpg" alt="rachel" width="500" height="332" /></a>\n\n<a title="rachel by elle_effect, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/elle_effect/2434997725/"><img src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3236/2434997725_33bca0e37f.jpg" alt="rachel" width="500" height="332" /></a>\n\nTonight = good. Crepes, cloves, good friends, old museum overlooking the city, conversation, love... yes, <strong>good.</strong>\n\nband of horses, anathallo and andrew bird - <em>you kinda own me right now</em>.\n\nenjoy your night -\nlauren', 'rachel', '', 'private', 'open', 'open', '', 'rachel', '', '', '2008-04-23 03:37:26', '2008-04-23 03:37:26', '', 0, 'http://laurensusanna.wordpress.com/?p=556', 0, 'post', '', 5);
INSERT INTO `wp_eqv5w1_posts` VALUES(558, 2, '2008-04-28 06:04:11', '2008-04-28 06:04:11', 'the lovely Katie:\n\n<a title="katie by elle_effect, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/elle_effect/2438972023/"><img src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2410/2438972023_0caa604c5f.jpg" alt="katie" width="332" height="500" /></a>\n\n<img src="http://i71.photobucket.com/albums/i122/elle_effect_photography/2447667125_62d418552d.jpg" alt="" />\n\nÂ \n\nÂ \n\nthe lovely Alli:Â \n\n<a title="Alli by elle_effect, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/elle_effect/2448446032/"><img src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3220/2448446032_8d2b5126b1.jpg" alt="Alli" width="332" height="500" /></a>\n\n<a title="Alli by elle_effect, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/elle_effect/2448476486/"><img src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3254/2448476486_d627e8290d.jpg" alt="Alli" width="332" height="500" /></a>\n\nÂ \n\nI''ll eventually catch you all up on life recently. Right now, I simply need to live it...Â \n\nfull house, again.\n-laurenÂ ', 'tis the season for senior portraits', '', 'private', 'open', 'open', '', 'tis-the-season-for-senior-portraits', '', '', '2008-04-28 06:04:11', '2008-04-28 06:04:11', '', 0, 'http://laurensusanna.wordpress.com/?p=558', 0, 'post', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `wp_eqv5w1_posts` VALUES(559, 2, '2008-04-29 17:07:36', '2008-04-29 17:07:36', '<p style="text-align:center;">Because of some technical difficulties concerning my domain, <strong>please redirect yourself to my updated blog by clicking below:Â </strong></p>\n<p style="text-align:center;"><span style="font-size:large;"><a href="http://laurensusanna.wordpress.com">http://laurensusanna.wordpress.com</a></span></p>\n<p style="text-align:center;">Â </p>\n<p style="text-align:center;">Thanks - sorry for the inconvenience!</p>\n<p style="text-align:center;">-lauren : )</p>\n<span style="font-size:large;"> </span>\nÂ \n\nÂ \n\nÂ \n\nÂ \n\nÂ \n\nÂ \n\nÂ \n\n"end of april update:"\n\nSitting with<a href="http://jessicagrady.wordpress.com"> Jessica</a> in Taylor Books- local coffee shop here in Charleston. Not my favorite place, but it works. A senior shoot got rained out this morning and rescheduled it for tomorrow - getting everything ready for the wedding this weekend and crossing my fingers that my lens shows up in the mail tonight as planned.Â \n\nBeen finishing up editing shoots from the past month or so - finally done. End of the month... tying up loose ends... feels good.Â \n\nSaw my sister''s dress rehearsal last night for her ballet performance, "The Little Mermaid." Looks like in the coming month there will be some more <a href="http://flickr.com/photos/elle_effect/sets/72157604790070515/">dance portraits</a> on the way! Really looking forward to working with more company dancers from around here - dance + photography, mmm - what could be better? : )Â \n\nA few more from <a href="http://myspace.com/elizabethstanley">Liz Stanley''s</a> model shoot:Â \n\n<a title="liz stanley by elle_effect, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/elle_effect/2451680859/"><img src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2249/2451680859_ac824fdd4e.jpg" alt="liz stanley" width="333" height="500" /></a>\n\n<a title="liz stanley by elle_effect, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/elle_effect/2452510302/"><img src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2006/2452510302_497f7e22de.jpg" alt="liz stanley" width="500" height="500" /></a>\n\n<a title="liz stanley by elle_effect, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/elle_effect/2452511146/"><img src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2286/2452511146_037d251220.jpg" alt="liz stanley" width="500" height="333" /></a>\n\nÂ \n\nWe picked up the old canvas frames in a trash bin and spray painted them. Really liked how they turned out in the photo and how we hung them in the trees.Â \n\nÂ \n\nspeak with sharpness, integrity and truth -\nlaurenÂ \n\nÂ \n\nÂ \n\nÂ ', 'UNTIL FURTHER NOTICE -', '', 'private', 'open', 'open', '', 'end-of-april-update', '', '', '2008-04-29 17:07:36', '2008-04-29 17:07:36', '', 0, 'http://laurensusanna.wordpress.com/?p=559', 0, 'post', '', 1);
