INSERT INTO `wp_eqv5w1_posts` VALUES(565, 2, '2008-05-10 16:16:37', '2008-05-10 16:16:37', '-I am learning to balance professional and personal life. It''s not as easy as I would like it to be.\n\n-Balance is key. In everything. This simple truth never, ever changes.\n\n-I recently have had a strong desire to never be too far from a large body of water. And to kayak. A lot.\n\n-If gas gets any higher, I''m getting a motorcycle. Call me names if you wish.\n\n-My heart is tired, weak yet strong at the same time. Maybe this is what God meant for us to know when he said, "when you are weak, I am strong." I''m there.\n\n-I am growing rapidly. I feel I''m walking the tightrope of girl and woman continually, never fully one or the other.\n\n-I''m more aggressive than I used to be. I see it, I seek it, I do it, I''m there. I''m trying not to think or question too much... just enough.\n\n-I am now scheduling shoots for winter. And have been booking summer/fall months since late Feb. Times flies. I remember the beginning of all of this and appreciate it, and it keeps me grounded.\n\n-I enjoyed living without my cell phone and wireless internet all weekend. Wireless was available at the local Port City Java, but I opted not to. I opted to keep my cell phone off or away. I opted to sit on a balcony every morning and late afternoon when I had a moment reading, I opted to lay on the beach at midnight and clearly see the stars without city lights, I opted to take long night exposures as well - which will eventually be posted.\n\n-I may elope. Kind of want to. Sort of want to. Most likely won''t. Probably would regret it. But it has crossed my mind. My wedding will probably be the most unorthodox thing you''ll go to. You won''t know what''s coming next.\n\nI didn''t even put a dent in the wedding photos, but I did ONE today - I came home to 4 shoots to finish, so they had to wait. But I''m eager to really work on them and get them up. Breathtaking wedding. <a href="http://www.airliegardens.org/">Airlie Gardens</a>, Wilmington, NC. Stories and photos to come.\n\n<a title="Untitled by elle_effect, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/elle_effect/2474870874/"><img src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3061/2474870874_ec88e00639.jpg" alt="" width="333" height="500" /></a>\n\nMy sister turned 15 yesterday. She can drive. Umm, haha. Love her so.\n\nGood thing the storm held off a day:  <a title="driving into the storm by elle_effect, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/elle_effect/2473452415/"><img src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2146/2473452415_65cf978e33.jpg" alt="driving into the storm" width="500" height="332" /></a> <a title="Untitled by elle_effect, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/elle_effect/2473452417/"><img src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2006/2473452417_d4f4029309.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="332" /></a> <a title="Untitled by elle_effect, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/elle_effect/2473452411/"><img src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2150/2473452411_761a0d1de2.jpg" alt="" width="332" height="500" /></a>\n\nAnd we enjoyed the end of the reception after a long day of work:  <img src="http://i71.photobucket.com/albums/i122/elle_effect_photography/2474284352_4991265802.jpg" alt="" />\n\nalso a massive upload on <a href="http://flickr.com/photos/elle_effect">flickr</a> for you to enjoy. : ) -lauren', 'a few things:', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'a-few-things', '', '', '2008-05-10 16:16:37', '2008-05-10 16:16:37', '', 0, 'http://laurensusanna.wordpress.com/?p=565', 0, 'post', '', 2);
INSERT INTO `wp_eqv5w1_posts` VALUES(567, 2, '2008-05-17 23:59:20', '2008-05-17 23:59:20', '<p style="text-align:center;">Â taken friday evening; 8:30PM; downtown Charleston, WV\n<a title="30PM by elle_effect, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/elle_effect/2497879735/"></a>\nÂ </p>\n<p style="text-align:center;"><img class="aligncenter" src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2162/2497879735_0de9af3418.jpg" alt="30PM" width="500" height="332" /></p>\nSo, as most of you know, laurenstonestreet.com was hacked about 2 weeks ago. I''m still in the process of fixing the whole ordeal.Â \n\nAs of now, the wonderful Amos Lanka and I will be chatting it up in the coming weeks making me an official website. It''s been underway for a little while, and now it''s finally coming to fruition. I''m thrilled. Be on the lookout. Since laurenstonestreet.com has been taken until further notice, looks like my new domain may be elleeffect.com or something of the sort.Â \n\nI love when I can pull up to the local Panera, not buy a thing, and sit on the patio and steal/borrow their wireless. Stopped by on my way to see a movie with the family tonight - Narnia dos.Â \n\nStill editing tons of wedding photos from Brentley and Jodi''s wedding - <em>they will be up soon for all you wanting and anxious to buy! : )Â </em>\n\nThe next couple of weeks are booked for me, too. There are some <em>fun</em>Â things up my sleeve/going on the next month that I''ll let you all in on here soon (maybe, ha!).Â \n\nÂ \n\nAs for now, movie in 5. Haven''t been to a movie in... a very long time.Â \n\nÂ \n\n-laurenÂ ', 'quick update sitting at panera -', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'quick-update-sitting-at-panera', '', '', '2008-05-17 23:59:20', '2008-05-17 23:59:20', '', 0, 'http://laurensusanna.wordpress.com/?p=567', 0, 'post', '', 7);
INSERT INTO `wp_eqv5w1_posts` VALUES(568, 2, '2008-05-24 04:44:29', '2008-05-24 04:44:29', '<p style="text-align:center;"><a title="a fresh start by elle_effect, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/elle_effect/2517270416/"><img class="aligncenter" src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3241/2517270416_1b89a6d98d.jpg" alt="a fresh start" width="500" height="332" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align:center;">Â </p>\n<p style="text-align:center;">Â </p>\n<p style="text-align:center;">There have been tons of new photos I''ve been working on lately. I''ve been stepping back a bit from doing so many shoots and have been trying new things, redefining what it means for me to be a photographer. I''ve discovered new things about myself, about photography and my direction. This is definitely going to be an exciting year, and I know that uploads have been sparse on flickr and on my blog - but in time, you''ll be seeing my progress and I''ll do my best to keep you updated along the way. I''d love for you to join me on this journey and give advice - and maybe, even more of our paths will cross in the near future. Thanks so much for support thus far.</p>\nÂ \n<p style="text-align:left;">A few things planned on the calendar:Â </p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>June is looking to be a month off for me with close friends and family doing some traveling along with some needed solitude.</li>\n	<li>Tentatively heading to Medellin, Columbia, South America in July. Keep me in your prayers about this. I would be working with Open Arms Foundation shooting some much needed photos for their upcoming website, which, I would love to give the opportunity to one of my web designer friends (you?) in helping them out with a new, simple website so the world can stay connected with what they''re doing. If you''re interested, <a href="mailto:elle_effect@mac.com">contact me</a>. Their organization is community-based and has stood the test of time in getting the hundreds and hundred of boys off the streets and through a process to where they can go back into society with a trade learned (agriculture is huge there) and ready to face the world new. I could go on and on.Â </li>\n	<li>In August I will be heading to the 10-day Ad Deum Dance Intensive in Houston, TX. I will be pursuing more opportunities that have opened up with dance photography and of course, dance. Hopefully, I will be performing a personally choreographed solo or duet piece throughout that time.Â </li>\n	<li>For the month of Sept, I will be inÂ Modjadjiskloof (also known asÂ Duiwelskloof), South Africa with <a href="http://pfunanane.org/">Pfunanane Academy</a> alongside, Sarah Deppen-Haver. I will documenting my time there in both photographs and writing and also to help with the end of the year concert they put on annually. I''ve heard some of the incredible and heart wrenching stories of the kids there. Read their frequently updated blog <a href="http://www.pfunanane.blogspot.com/">here</a>. I desperately need your help in getting there. I need to raise $5,000 to go, travel where I''m needed, updating the photo gear I need to make this trip and some to simply give to the Academy. I''m in the process of making photo books to sell in the next couple of weeks.Â </li>\n</ul>\n<div style="text-align:center;">So, as you can see, some exciting things are coming up. Also, a little side note - the sky has been absolutely breathtaking on a continual basis, and I''m going to start documenting it on a continual basis and share it with you.Â </div>\n<p style="text-align:center;"><a title="night sky by elle_effect, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/elle_effect/2517911158/"><img class="aligncenter" src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2122/2517911158_3b54f8965d.jpg" alt="night sky" width="332" height="500" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align:center;">Â </p>\n<p style="text-align:center;"><a title="evening sky by elle_effect, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/elle_effect/2517911074/"><img class="aligncenter" src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2107/2517911074_d70b864bed.jpg" alt="evening sky" width="500" height="333" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align:center;">Â </p>\n\n<p style="text-align:center;">stay tuned-\nlaurenÂ </p>', 'a fresh start', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'a-fresh-start', '', '', '2008-05-24 04:44:29', '2008-05-24 04:44:29', '', 0, 'http://laurensusanna.wordpress.com/?p=568', 0, 'post', '', 1);
INSERT INTO `wp_eqv5w1_posts` VALUES(569, 2, '2008-05-30 03:03:24', '2008-05-30 03:03:24', '<p style="text-align:center;"><a title="cape fear by elle_effect, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/elle_effect/2535621806/"><img src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2367/2535621806_ac437f9431.jpg" alt="cape fear" width="500" height="387" /></a></p>\n\n<p style="text-align:center;">cape fear\nwilmington, NCÂ </p>', '&gt;&gt;', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '569', '', '', '2008-05-30 03:03:24', '2008-05-30 03:03:24', '', 0, 'http://laurensusanna.wordpress.com/?p=569', 0, 'post', '', 4);
INSERT INTO `wp_eqv5w1_posts` VALUES(570, 2, '2008-06-04 02:40:44', '2008-06-04 02:40:44', 'And I don''t feel guilty about it.\n\nThe past few weeks (months, really) are pretty hard to explain. A lot of long pauses between sentences... actually, simply put it''s been a time of margin, of pauses, of endings and of change. <em>Fresh.</em>Â I feel like a new woman and I''m stepping into a complete new season of life - something I''d more than love to keep a mystery. It''s the mystery of my God that keeps me pursuing, that keeps me guessing, that keeps me falling in love with Him even more. I''d say, He''s a pretty wise guy for that. No chance you''ll ever be bored. ; )Â \n\nSo, in time, I''ll unveil the things going on in my heart and in my life. I''m home in West Virginia, I''ve joined a running club (Couch to 5K!) and I jog/run 3+ miles every other day. I walk to the local Tim Hortons where there are some great employees that make my day. I get a bagel and cream cheese with an iced coffee almost every day. I''m spending time with two beautiful young girls, Brittany and Tabitha, while some hardship is going on in the community. I''m learning the value of community and how faithful I''ve been loved by people around here... I''m amazed. There have been dinner parties, bonfires, jam sessions, walks, picnics; people have stayed so late over here they crash on the couch : ) It''s been incredible and exactly what I''ve needed. I went back to sports therapy for a check up after 6 months - no more issues from past dance injuries; <em>so</em> good to hear. I''m training again for a dance intensive this summer in August and I''ve been choreographing a 7 minute piece toÂ Saeglopur by Sigur Ros (off the Takk album). I''ve missed the art form of movement... and from my time off from it, it''s come back even stronger and I feel more alive than ever.Â \n\nRight now, my main focus is not about ''making money.'' The only reason I make money is to do the things I love, to support those I love and to well, live - because apparently, the world revolves around money and you simply can''t live without it. It''s not my driving force, it''s okay if for a month I "get by." I am learning, I am more confident than I ever have been, I am challenging myself, pushing myself - but also, taking margin, reflecting, refining my art and <em>why</em>Â I create it in the first place. I''m learning to walk and live in these checks and balances... and well, literally, too... <em>checks</em>Â and<em>Â balances</em>. Ha.Â \n\nÂ \n\nI''m digging into a lot of suggested reads and would love if you had a few of your favorites to throw my way. As of late, I''m also enjoying <a href="http://myspace.com/grizzlybear">Grizzly Bear</a>, <a href="http://myspace.com/midlake">Midlake</a>, Mum, Jeff Tweedy, The Cinematic Orchestra (esp ''to build a home'') and the new and old of <a href="http://myspace.com/theweepies">The Weepies</a> (been a favorite for quite awhile). Also, thanks to the love affair Dan had with Mary Oliver the first day I met him, I''ve begun more of one as well. She''s in the daily reads now and finishing <a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=hNwHN3mQmWoC&amp;dq=inauthor:Wendell+inauthor:Berry">The Art of Commonplace by Wendell Berry</a>. More than anything I''ve been digging into <a href="http://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=2%20Corinthians%204:16-19;&amp;version=47;">this</a>.\n\nÂ \n\nAlso, had a great time this past weekend hanging out and catching up with some old friends-\n\n<a title="Ryan, Andrew &amp; I by elle_effect, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/elle_effect/2540577930/"><img src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3095/2540577930_70795c0c19.jpg" alt="Ryan, Andrew &amp; I" width="500" height="332" /></a>\n\n<a title="Arian Jalali by elle_effect, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/elle_effect/2540053372/"><img src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3142/2540053372_c3ef2fc57f.jpg" alt="Arian Jalali" width="332" height="500" /></a>\n\n<a title="Lauren Cole by elle_effect, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/elle_effect/2540052600/"><img src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3272/2540052600_fa480f1350.jpg" alt="Lauren Cole" width="500" height="332" /></a>\n\nÂ \n\nÂ \n\nI''ll try and be more consistent in my posting ; )Â \n\nÂ \n\nlove all of you.\n-lauren\n\nÂ \n\nPS: preparation for South Africa is even more underway. details to come : )Â \n\nÂ \n\nÂ ', 'A post long overdue -', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'a-post-long-overdue', '', '', '2008-06-04 02:40:44', '2008-06-04 02:40:44', '', 0, 'http://laurensusanna.wordpress.com/?p=570', 0, 'post', '', 4);
