INSERT INTO `wp_eqv5w1_posts` VALUES(790, 2, '2008-10-14 13:32:24', '2008-10-14 13:32:24', '<strong>Three days</strong>.\n\nÂ \n\nMy life has utterly changed in the process of preparation for this trip. I''m not even sure where to begin. Even though I most definitely haven''t been writing in here Â (apologies), I''ve been writing faithfully anything and everything that happens, quotes, encouragement, nights where I can''t sleep and lists in my journal. Probably the next time I blog after this will be in South Africa. I leave Friday. My heart has been ready for weeks and my closest friends tell me there''s been a change in my eyes. I know there has. This is the first of many. There''s already need in Medellin, Colombia in February and talk of need in Uruguay. I''m diving into independent photojournalism and uncharted territory. I''m split 80% excited, 20% anxious, which I''m finding completely normal and expected.\n\n<a href="http://mynameisharry.com">Harry</a> came to visit this past week from England. He''ll be in the states for a few weeks. He was one of the best assistants I''ve had when I shot a wedding this past weekend. Perfect weekend for driving, as it was peak.Â \n<p style="text-align:center;">A little scouting the night before:</p>\n<p style="text-align:center;"><img class="aligncenter" src="http://i281.photobucket.com/albums/kk213/elle_effect/2929855817_d56b40cfac.jpg" alt="" /></p>\n<p style="text-align:center;"><img class="aligncenter" src="http://i281.photobucket.com/albums/kk213/elle_effect/2930708364_295b7e585d.jpg" alt="" /></p>\n<p style="text-align:center;"><img class="aligncenter" src="http://i281.photobucket.com/albums/kk213/elle_effect/2930713588_6f0ff24210.jpg" alt="" /></p>\n<p style="text-align:center;">(photos by Harry)</p>\n<p style="text-align:center;">Â </p>\n<p style="text-align:center;"><strong>Note</strong>: portraits at high noon after a morning wedding can be a challenge. I''m happy with how these turned out. Deidra and Isaac are an incredible couple and a pleasure to work with : )</p>\n<p style="text-align:center;"><a title="Deidra &amp; Isaac by elle_effect, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/elle_effect/2939907939/"><img class="aligncenter" src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3144/2939907939_5dd8ac8407.jpg" alt="Deidra &amp; Isaac" width="500" height="373" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align:center;"><a title="Deidra &amp; Isaac by elle_effect, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/elle_effect/2939902833/"><img class="aligncenter" src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3002/2939902833_27009aec2f.jpg" alt="Deidra &amp; Isaac" width="500" height="335" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align:center;"><a title="Deidra &amp; Isaac by elle_effect, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/elle_effect/2940755702/"><img class="aligncenter" src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3026/2940755702_6bf5111e57.jpg" alt="Deidra &amp; Isaac" width="500" height="335" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align:center;"><a title="CC_4 by elle_effect, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/elle_effect/2941706808/"><img class="aligncenter" src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3280/2941706808_02c1e073b2.jpg" alt="CC_4" width="500" height="335" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align:center;"><a title="CC_3 by elle_effect, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/elle_effect/2941705506/"><img class="aligncenter" src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3212/2941705506_ffecf84319.jpg" alt="CC_3" width="335" height="500" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align:center;">Â </p>\n<p style="text-align:center;"><a title="CC_5 by elle_effect, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/elle_effect/2941707342/"><img class="aligncenter" src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3205/2941707342_6bb5ca0a2b.jpg" alt="CC_5" width="335" height="500" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align:center;">Â </p>\n<p style="text-align:center;">All the fundraising, meetings, calls and lists are finished... now it''s time to gather, sleep somehow, and go. I want to thank each and every one of you who have come alongside me in this - my heart has been so deeply edified and encouraged by you. All the emails, letters, purchased prints and selfless giving of your time have made it possible for me to go. You''re all going with me in heart and what you give won''t come back void. Thank you.Â </p>\n<p style="text-align:center;">Â </p>\n<p style="text-align:center;">See you in Africa.</p>\n<p style="text-align:center;">-lauren</p>', 'Down to Three.', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'down-to-three', '', '', '2008-10-14 13:32:24', '2008-10-14 13:32:24', '', 0, 'http://laurensusanna.wordpress.com/?p=790', 0, 'post', '', 8);
INSERT INTO `wp_eqv5w1_posts` VALUES(792, 2, '2008-10-19 12:12:24', '2008-10-19 12:12:24', 'After 20+ hours of air time and 5 hours of driving time, I''m here. I won''t be updating very much, though, mostly words... not many photos... due to the internet situation (which, I''m thankful for, a 7-week major break from technology, what would be better?)\n\nDay one and not much to update you on.\n\nLots of reading, writing in the journal and solitude to come. Each day is going to bring new adventures.\n\nI like seeing monkeys out the kitchen window. At least for now ; )\n\n-lauren', 'Hello, from South Africa', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'hello-from-south-africa', '', '', '2008-10-19 12:12:24', '2008-10-19 12:12:24', '', 0, 'http://laurensusanna.wordpress.com/?p=792', 0, 'post', '', 4);
INSERT INTO `wp_eqv5w1_posts` VALUES(794, 2, '2008-10-23 19:10:14', '2008-10-23 19:10:14', '<p>It''s been an incredible week... Nate and I have been soaking in and adapting to culture and school life and just beginning to document. We''ve got time, so we''re taking our time and doing our best to live in to every moment.</p>\n<p>The kids are absolutely incredible. Can''t relay it to you enough. The first 2 days I was here, I jumped right into teaching (unexpectedly, but a cool surprise) the 2nd grade class (or simply, grade 2). They are hilarious. They learned my name and I''m still learning all of theirs - but I am known as "teacher, teacher" - definitely privileged to be called that ; )</p>\n<p>This week, we''ve been to a boys soccer match and girls net ball match between schools, started learning the ins and outs of the school community concert coming up on Nov 11th (and putting together props/sets - which includes painting and wood frames), experienced the church we''ll be at for the next 6 weeks and <em>grocery shopping</em>. I''d have to say our first attempt was hilarious. Sunday, our first day here, we realized eventually that everything was backwards. You know how you''d normally walk down the right side of the aisle? Nope... left. Just the same as how they drive.Â  ; ) The currency exchange rate is crazy good for us, and is easy to calculate considering it''s practically divided by 10. (R19.95 = $1.95, R450 = $45 and so on...)</p>\n<p>As my dad always says, "the morning starts in the evening" -- and I''ve definitely been experiencing that on a new level. The evenings after 8 or so are quiet... (like right now)... and there''s so much time for reflection, reading, writing, silence... needless to say, it''s been beautiful. Plus, after a long, good day with a bunchhh of crazy rad kids, it''s nice. I''ve needed this change and I''m longing for more of it, which I know will come in time while I''m here.</p>\n<p>He''s speaking, and I''m continuing to learn to listen.</p>\n<p>I''ll elaborate more as time progresses... as for now, some needed reflection before I write to you more.</p>\n<p>God is good.</p>\n<p>-lauren</p>\n<p>(pictures to come soon when I can, promise.)</p>', 'A week has almost finished...', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'a-week-has-almost-finished', '', '', '2008-10-23 19:10:14', '2008-10-23 19:10:14', '', 0, 'http://laurensusanna.wordpress.com/?p=794', 0, 'post', '', 2);
