INSERT INTO `wp_eqv5w1_posts` VALUES(1088, 2, '2009-09-10 21:27:48', '2009-09-10 21:27:48', 'I''m officially a resident of Cleveland, Ohio. I hear the winter is bitter. I feel peace in my new apartment. I''ve already had two guests - Adam &amp; Kate - in my first few days of living here. My house reminds me of Shrine Mont. I''m drinking a lot of tea, bananas and couscous. I figured out my locks. I''m writing new music and singing more than I used to. I''m getting better at guitar... since there is no piano, I am forced, and welcome that forcing. I''m enjoying classes - seeing how much I have to work on - hence, why I''m here in the first place.\n\nI thought I would never be able to dance again after my injuries. And here I am. What do I have to loose? Absolutely nothing.\n\nTackling streets in Cleveland to get to where I need to go... and surviving. I drive a van. A gold van, at that. Coolest girl on the block... maybe ; ) My roommate, Lori, is fabulous. We killed too many bugs today. I don''t like bugs. I have an amazing office space with french doors to call my own. Now, to move it all in and work in it! Taking it all one day at a time.\n\nStill somewhat in a state of shock, which is expected. My life changed drastically in one weekend.\n\nSo, here I am. Sitting at my dining room table given to me by Keta, sitting in a chair found in a random garage, thrilled to have wireless in the house finally, listening to Bon Iver with soft, evening light seeping through the surrounding windows. <strong>Here''s to a new beginning. </strong>\n<p style="text-align:center;"><a href="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2596/3907225031_62ec2b376a_b.jpg"><img class="aligncenter" src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2596/3907225031_62ec2b376a.jpg" alt="" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align:center;"><strong>(CLICK FOR LARGE VIEW)</strong></p>\n\n<strong>1. </strong>Packing the Uhaul in West Virginia\n<strong>2.</strong> Playing Snurts with Caitlin at my dining room table.\n<strong>3.</strong> Stephen moving things into the living room!\n<strong>4.</strong> My green, cozy bedroom.\n<strong>5.</strong> Stephen the night we arrived. Late.\n<strong>6.</strong> Hallway into dining room --&gt; living room --&gt; office.\n<strong>7.</strong> Me, at the end of a long day of moving + rearranging.\n<strong>8.</strong> Front of my apartment: via Stephen''s iPhone... as they left.\n<strong>9.</strong> My sister''s and my feet first night here.\n<p style="text-align:center;"></p>\n<p style="text-align:center;"></p>\n\n<p style="text-align:center;">First guests, <a href="http://myspace.com/adamtaylormusic">Adam</a> and Kate on their way through finishing out their month tour PA --&gt; Portland --&gt; PA.\nA few photos of them crashing in my living room:\n<img src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3452/3907105599_9ccfa8f465.jpg" alt="" />\n<img src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2445/3907883910_68648991b7.jpg" alt="" />\n<p style="text-align:center;"></p>\n<p style="text-align:center;">-L</p>', 'Life in Cleveland Thus Far', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'life-in-cleveland-thus-far', '', '', '2009-09-10 21:27:48', '2009-09-10 21:27:48', '', 0, 'http://elleeffect.com/?p=1088', 0, 'post', '', 5);
